name: Goa Giri Campuhan waterfall

review 1: As of early September the waterfall is almost empty! Itâ€™s a bit of a walk in dry rice fields and then down steep steps and finally a dark cave. No entrance fee as there are no tourists. Goa Raja was much better!
review 2: Absolutely stunning walk to get to the waterfalls. Great pools for swimming with crystal clear water.
review 3: We come here to climb up the falls and explore further into the forest to see what's around the corner. It's a fun little spot.
